Amazon is competing with tech giants like Microsoft and Alphabet to build AI data centers, increasing demand for high-end processors, particularly those from Nvidia. Amazon Web Services (AWS) is being utilized by Debenhams Group to accelerate its adoption of artificial intelligence (AI). Analyze the impact Analyze the impact AMZN upcoming earnings ﻿ ﻿ Next report date — Report period Q2 2025 EPS estimate 1.32 USD Revenue estimate ‪161.97 B‬ USD Key stats ﻿ ﻿ Market capitalization ‪2.37 T‬ USD Dividend yield (indicated) — Price to earnings Ratio (TTM) 35.87 Basic EPS (TTM) 6.26 USD Net income (FY) ‪59.25 B‬ USD Revenue (FY) ‪637.96 B‬ USD Shares float ‪9.49 B‬ Beta (1Y) 1.37 Employees ﻿ ﻿ Employees (FY) ‪1.56 M‬ Change (1Y) ‪+31 K‬ +2.03% Revenue / Employee (1Y) ‪410.00 K‬ USD Net income / Employee (1Y) ‪38.08 K‬ USD About Amazon.com ﻿ Sector Retail Trade Industry Internet Retail CEO Andrew R. Jassy Website aboutamazon.com Headquarters Seattle Founded 1994 FIGI BBG000BVPV84 Amazon.com, Inc. engages in the provision of online retail shopping services. It operates through the following business segments: North America, International, and Amazon Web Services (AWS). The North America segment includes retail sales of consumer products and subscriptions through North America-focused websites such as amazon.com and amazon.ca. The International segment offers retail sales of consumer products and subscriptions through internationally-focused websites. The Amazon Web Services segment involves in the global sales of compute, storage, database, and AWS service offerings for start-ups, enterprises, government agencies, and academic institutions. The company was founded by Jeffrey P. Bezos in July 1994 and is headquartered in Seattle, WA. Show more Related stocks ﻿ Check out other big names from the same industry as AMZN.
